output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of Allied health, 5 years after graduation, Accommodation and food service activities was the most common industry for and White ethnicity graduates, Transportation and storage was the most common industry for and Black ethnicity graduates, Education was the most common industry for and Asian ethnicity graduates, Administrative and support service activities was the most common industry for Mixed and Other ethnicity graduates, and Financial and insurance activities was the most common industry for and Not known ethnicity graduates.

The industry with the largest range in proportions was Administrative and support service activities where Other ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and Asian ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion.The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Other service activities where White ethnicity graduates the highest median earnings (£27,800) and Asian ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£22,600).The group with the highest median earnings was White ethnicity graduates in the Other service activities industry (median earnings of £27,800).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of Allied health by ethnicity, five years after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
